<subSubSection id="02C66578FFF9FFB8FF3D9F326B95794E" pageId="20" pageNumber="34" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFF9FFB8FF3D9F326B2F7ECF" blockId="20.[151,756,886,1072]" pageId="20" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFF9FFB8FF3D9F3268057EEF" bold="true" box="[151,264,886,910]" pageId="20" pageNumber="34">Remarks:</emphasis>
It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="8DDC4D70FFF9FFB8FE739F336B627EEF" box="[473,623,886,910]" class="Nodosariata" family="Nodosariidae" genus="Nodosaria" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nodosariida" pageId="20" pageNumber="34" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="latejugata">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFF9FFB8FE739F336B627EEF" box="[473,623,886,910]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="34">N. latejugata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in rapidly decreasing in chamber size as added.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFF9FFB8FF3D9FF26B95794E" blockId="20.[151,756,886,1072]" pageId="20" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFF9FFB8FF3D9FF268D87EAF" bold="true" box="[151,469,950,974]" pageId="20" pageNumber="34">Stratigraphic distribution:</emphasis>
It is recorded in the Maastrichtian and Paleocene by LUGER (1985). It is rare to moderate in the Maastrichtian zones and it is floody in the Paleocene zones of the Esh El Mallaha area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
